==2009 Festival==   
The 2009 World Science Festival took place from June 9 thru 14. Its opening night was a celebration of the 80th birthday of [[E. O. Wilson]], was co-chaired by Alan Alda, [[Glenn Close]] and [[Harrison Ford]], and featuring performances by [[Yo Yo Ma]], [[Joshua Bell]], and others.<ref>[http://www.worldsciencefestival.com/2009/opening Opening Night Gala Performance] page on the WSF Website, last accessed 2009-06-04.</ref> The more than 30 main events of the festival included an evening about [[time]] with neurologist [[Oliver Sacks]] and psychologist [[Daniel Gilbert]], Alan Alda exploring the nature of innovative breakthroughs with inventor [[Dean Kamen]] and the director of the [[MIT]] Mechatronics Lab, [[Hugh Herr]]. One of the highlights of the event was a panel discussion on intelligent machines involving, on the one hand, [[Battlestar Galactica]] cast members [[Michael Hogan (Canadian actor)|Michael Hogan]], [[Mary McDonnell]], and on the other, robot researcher [[Hod Lipson]] and cyberneticist [[Kevin Warwick]].<ref>[http://www.worldsciencefestival.com/2009/all-events-by-date 2009 Events by date] on the WSF website, last accessed 2009-06-04.</ref> 

